// S1FPacketSetExperience (0x1F) - Set Experience
// Direction: CLIENTBOUND | State: PLAY
// Handler: NetHandlerPlayClient.handleSetExperience()
// Handler interface: INetHandlerPlayClient
//
// This packet is received by the vanilla NetHandlerPlayClient and processed
// by the corresponding handle* method. No hacked client module in the
// examined codebases (Rise 6.0, Jigsaw 0.26, RektSky B5, Sigma 4.11,
// Memeware 7.3, Aqua 13, and 490+ others) directly targets this specific
// packet for modification or cancellation.
//
// The vanilla handler simply updates the client state and does not offer
// any competitive advantage when intercepted.
//
// Packet fields:
// experienceBar: float - Progress to next level (0.0-1.0)
// totalExperience: VarInt - Total accumulated XP
// level: VarInt - Current XP level
